<subSubSection id="C36965D095671876FF0BB0A711231F21" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95671876FF0BB0A711231F21" blockId="3.[174,1233,1337,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
D i a g n o s i s. Wingspan about 
<quantity id="4C8B9BBE95671876FD8DB0A711FA1CA1" box="[613,703,1434,1460]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
. Head pale grey or whitish-grey, the scales projecting in front like two tufts. Labial palpi long, bent, pale grey, second joint is densely tufted. Forewings elongate, grey with numerous very small black dots arranged in four irregular rows; a dark lines goes round the apex of the wing to the anal angle (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FBC5B0C7172C1F01" box="[1069,1129,1530,1556]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FB9CB0C717C71F01" box="[1140,1154,1530,1556]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1408,1430]" captionTargetBox="[325,1069,174,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-159@1.[321,1078,171,1383]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Argyresthia kurenzovi: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral view, 3 — ventral plate, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — female genitalia; 6 — bursa copulatrix with signum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414497/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995671876FB9CB0C717C71F01" box="[1140,1154,1530,1556]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Cilia grey. Hind, wings and their cilia grey.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36965D095671876FF0BB30712AB1FE1" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95671876FF0BB30711E21F61" blockId="3.[174,1233,1337,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FE77B307129A1F41" box="[415,479,1594,1620]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FE18B30712BB1F41" box="[496,510,1594,1620]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995671876FE18B30712BB1F41" box="[496,510,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FDE7B30711581F41" box="[527,541,1594,1620]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995671876FDE7B30711581F41" box="[527,541,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Saccus less than twice as long as valva. Aedeagus with 3 cornuti, more than twice as long as valva.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95671876FF0BB34712AB1FE1" blockId="3.[174,1233,1337,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FE5BB34712B51F81" box="[435,496,1658,1684]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FE15B347114E1F81" box="[509,523,1658,1684]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995671876FE15B347114E1F81" box="[509,523,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95671876FDF2B347116D1F81" box="[538,552,1658,1684]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[331,1074,184,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-183@5.[326,1083,166,1269]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 5. Pseudoplutella porrectella: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (lateral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414511/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995671876FDF2B347116D1F81" box="[538,552,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Lobes of vaginal plate moderate and not closely to each other. Apophyses posterior shorter than apophyses anterior. Dorsal branch of apophyses anterior shorter than their common stem. Ductus bursae with sclerotization. 
<collectingRegion id="49B7F8B995671876FB65B38717951FC1" box="[1165,1232,1722,1748]" country="Turkey" name="Bursa" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Bursa</collectingRegion>
copulatrix without signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36965D095671871FF0BB3C7101A1C14" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95671876FF0BB3C710FE1E21" blockId="3.[174,1233,1337,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">R e m a r k s. This species can be easily recognized by its above mentioned external characters as well as by the structures of male and female genitalia.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0C66D395601871FF42B6E311591D1A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" startId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" targetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95601871FF42B6E311591D1A" blockId="4.[170,1228,990,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 4. 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895601871FF04B6E312E31AE6" baseAuthorityName="Stainton" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[236,422,990,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Kessleria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxifragae">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FF04B6E312E31AE6" box="[236,422,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Kessleria saxifragae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FE5AB6E312F81AE6" box="[434,445,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">1</emphasis>
— moth (habitus, dorsal); 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FD2DB6E311951AE6" box="[709,720,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">2</emphasis>
— male genitalia (ventral view); 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FBFBB6E3175B1AE6" box="[1043,1054,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">3</emphasis>
— aedeagus; 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FB4CB6E317EA1AE6" box="[1188,1199,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">4</emphasis>
— female genitalia; 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FEA4B6C412121D1B" box="[332,343,1017,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">5</emphasis>
— bursa copulatrix.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95601871FF33B17A10FC1DF4" blockId="4.[166,1225,1095,1282]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
According to Sattler &amp; Tremevan (1973): “The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895601871FCA5B17A108C1D74" box="[845,969,1095,1121]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Paradoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FCA5B17A108C1D74" box="[845,969,1095,1121]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been erroneously attributed to Millière by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE24BAA95601871FE28B15A111E1D97" author="Friese, G." box="[448,603,1127,1154]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 131" refId="ref2465" refString="Friese, G. 1960. Revision der Palaarktischen Yponomeutidae unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Genitalien (Lepidoptera). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 10 (1 / 2), 1 - 131." type="journal article" year="1960">Friese (1960)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895601871FD8CB15A11A51D94" box="[612,736,1127,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Paradoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FD8CB15A11A51D94" box="[612,736,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originated from Millière but was used and unintentionally made available by Stainton prior to its proposal and generic description by Millière”. Therefore although Stainton wrote in his papers “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895601871FCB6B19A17FA1DD4" authority="Milliere" authorityName="Milliere" authorityYear="1869" box="[862,1215,1191,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Paradoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osyridellus">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FCB6B19A171F1DD4" box="[862,1114,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Paradoxus osyridellus</emphasis>
Millière
</taxonomicName>
” the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895601871FEF2B1FA12D31DF4" box="[282,406,1223,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Paradoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FEF2B1FA12D31DF4" box="[282,406,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C734DD895601871FE38B1FA110F1DF4" authorityName="Milliere" authorityYear="1869" box="[464,586,1223,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Paradoxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osyridellus">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FE38B1FA110F1DF4" box="[464,586,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">osyridellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be attributed to Stainton.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95601871FF33B1DA101A1C14" blockId="4.[166,1225,1095,1282]" box="[219,863,1255,1282]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F36476CB95601871FE7BB1DA12B61C14" box="[403,499,1255,1281]" name="Ukraine" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(the 
<collectingRegion id="49B7F8B995601871FDD8B1DA11CF1C17" box="[560,650,1255,1282]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Crimea</collectingRegion>
) for the first time.
</paragraph>
